The paper presents a theoretical method for planning and controlling agile bipedal locomotion based on robustly tracking a set of non-periodic keyframe states. The methodology involves a hybrid phase-space planning and control method, a step transition solver, a robust hybrid automaton, a steering direction model, and a phase-space metric. These components suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves planning and control algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves simulations, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
